<p class="courseblocktitle"><strong>MUS 390.  Record Company Marketing and Operations.  3 hours.</strong></p>
<p class="courseblockdesc">
Study of marketing and operations practices employed by record companies. Understanding of analytic techniques used to inform marketing decisions. Analysis of music industry marketing research methodology. Survey of promotion practices. Course Information: Extensive computer use required. Field work required. Grade of C or better in <a href="/search/?P=MUS%20290" title="MUS 290" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'MUS 290');">MUS 290</a> and Grade of C or better in <a href="/search/?P=MUS%20202" title="MUS 202" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'MUS 202');">MUS 202</a> and Grade of C or better in <a href="/search/?P=MUS%20201" title="MUS 201" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'MUS 201');">MUS 201</a> and Grade of C or better in <a href="/search/?P=MUS%20270" title="MUS 270" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'MUS 270');">MUS 270</a> and Grade of C or better in <a href="/search/?P=MKTG%20360" title="MKTG 360" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'MKTG 360');">MKTG 360</a> and Grade of C or better in <a href="/search/?P=ACTG%20210" title="ACTG 210" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'ACTG 210');">ACTG 210</a>. Recommended background: Fluency in reading and performing music.<br/>
</p>
